</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulocz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Locz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/11/02 10:18:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=104.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Why I think the CH nerf is the root cause of the monk nerf</span><hr size=1> I think the cleric CH nerf is the reason behind the monk nerf.<br>
<br>
Here is why (and let's ignore the defensive discipline for now):<br>
Currently, once you exceed the AC softcap, what most differentiates the tanking ability of warriors from from monks is the number of HPs.  Warriors thus become superior tanks to monks primarily because they have more HPs which makes CHing more economical.<br>
<br>
Imagine PoP with no monk nerf, but CH was nerfed to 7500 HPs.  Also suppose monks and plate tanks all had 7500+ HPs.  So complete heal is no longer complete.  HPs beyond 7500 are not healed back except for the infrequent patch heal.  Thus, HPs over 7500 become less valuable than the first 7500.  If the ability to absorb damage were similar between a highest end warrior and a highest end monk, and both monks and warriors are only healed back to 7500 HPs during the CH-cycle, then the tanking advantage a warrior has over a monk is further diminished.<br>
<br>
I think this was the itch Verant wanted to scratch.<br>
<br>
A better solution to the &quot;monk&quot; problem would be to un-nerf CH, un-nerf monks, and limit the number of all/all items with high HPs.  This solution would allow warriors to gain a several-thousand HP advantage over monks, and allow that warrior HP advantage to be highly desirable in designing an economical CH cycle.  This better solution would still allow monks to enjoy the class attributes they currently have. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=312390 ">
Locz Agneyastra </a><BR>
Warder</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucuthulpaindancer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cuthul Paindancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grumpy Old Lizard</span><br>  Posts: 2165<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/11/02 10:35:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=104.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why I think the CH nerf is the root cause of the monk ne</span><hr size=1> Yep locz, you may have a point.<br>
